================================================================================
SECTION 1 — SUMMARY
================================================================================

The reflector repository is a research-grade, publication-infrastructure-first
repository hosting a single LaTeX manuscript titled "Reflector: Reflective
Development Systems for Recursive AI-Augmented Software Engineering." The
repository is currently in early draft status (v0.0.1). Phase 1 (repository
foundation and publication infrastructure) is marked complete in ROADMAP.md.

The overall architecture is coherent and well-intentioned. The publication
pipeline (LaTeX → PDF → GitHub Pages → GitHub Release → arXiv bundle) is
structurally complete and largely functional. CI/CD is automated using five
GitHub Actions workflows. Semantic versioning and conventional commits are
enforced.

However, the content layer (paper sections, bibliography, Python implementation,
demos) remains almost entirely scaffolded but unimplemented. Several
synchronization gaps exist between metadata files, workflows, and the deployed
site. One metadata inconsistency in the LaTeX source points to the wrong
repository URL. The CHANGELOG.md, required by the release workflow, does not
yet exist. The GitHub Pages hero image is not automatically copied to the
deployment site during the pages workflow.

This audit identifies these gaps and categorizes them to support future bounded
refinement passes.

