SECTION 3 — STRENGTHS
================================================================================

PUBLICATION INFRASTRUCTURE

  [+] Complete LaTeX build pipeline
      - latexmk + biber configured via root .latexmkrc
      - Build artifacts isolated to paper/.cache/ (gitignored)
      - PDF output at paper/.cache/out/paper.pdf
      - Shell build script (scripts/build-paper.sh) supports --open and --publish flags

  [+] Automated GitHub Pages deployment
      - Builds fresh PDF, copies to _site/, deploys via actions/deploy-pages@v4
      - SHA256 checksum verification between build output, docs/, and _site/
      - Cache-busting via GITHUB_SHA applied to index.html at deploy time
      - Publication manifest (docs/publication.json) generated at deploy time
      - Dual PDF routes: reflector.pdf and reflector-latest.pdf

  [+] Automated release pipeline
      - release-please creates semantic version PRs (config-driven)
      - release-paper.yml builds, bundles, and creates GitHub Releases on tag push
      - Generates both source bundle (.zip) and arXiv bundle (.zip)
      - Release manifest (JSON) with SHA256 checksums included
      - CHANGELOG.md and VERSION validation before release proceeds

  [+] Citation and metadata infrastructure
      - CITATION.cff v1.2.0 with ORCID identifier
      - release-please auto-updates CITATION.cff version via jsonpath
      - Placeholder DOI/arXiv/Zenodo fields clearly documented for future fill-in
      - publication.json and release-manifest.json provide structured metadata state

  [+] Developer experience
      - .editorconfig for consistent whitespace/encoding across all file types
      - Conventional commits enforced via commitlint (PR-gated)
      - Custom commit types: research, spec, sync, audit (domain-appropriate)
      - .gitignore covers Python, LaTeX, OS artifacts, editor artifacts comprehensively
      - .latexindent.yml for auto-formatting

CI/CD QUALITY

  [+] Minimal permissions principle applied (contents: read where possible)
  [+] fail-fast: false on matrix builds
  [+] Artifact upload on failure for debugging (build artifacts, 7-day retention)
  [+] Concurrency group on pages deployment prevents race conditions
  [+] xu-cheng/latex-action@v3 pinned to major version

PAPER STRUCTURE

  [+] Abstract is substantive (4 paragraphs, publication-ready draft)
  [+] Section topology is well-defined (16 sections, clear logical flow)
  [+] Intended figures documented inline per section (future-planning)
  [+] Excalidraw source diagrams present (3 files: system-overview,
      human-governance-checkpoints, recursive-audit-loop)
  [+] hero.png present as canonical publication preview asset
  [+] examples/ directory has two narrative example documents

FUTURE IMPLEMENTATION SCAFFOLDING

