SECTION 9 — IMPLEMENTATION OBSERVATIONS
================================================================================

The reflector/ Python package topology mirrors the paper section structure:
  - reflector/audits/         ↔  paper/sections/reflective_auditing.tex
  - reflector/synchronization/ ↔ paper/sections/synchronization.tex
  - reflector/orchestration/  ↔  paper/sections/milestone_execution.tex
  - reflector/schemas/        ↔  paper/sections/reflector_framework.tex
  - reflector/workflows/      ↔  paper/sections/reflector_framework.tex
  - reflector/cli/            ↔  operational tooling

This structural alignment is intentional and architecturally coherent.
The implementation scaffold is well-positioned to grow as the paper sections
are completed. Maintaining this traceability between paper concepts and
implementation modules will be valuable for future readers and contributors.

The .github/specs/reflector.spec.md contains detailed user stories and
acceptance scenarios that should guide the initial implementation pass.
Priority user story P1 (human-governed recursive development) maps most
directly to reflector/synchronization/ and reflector/orchestration/.

